141
01:28:40,000 --> 01:29:11,000
FALSE
This is based on the idea that Saroo's obsession with his search and his refusal to tell his parents drovea bit of a wedge between them. This seems to have been invented by the filmmakers. 
142
01:29:11,000 --> 01:30:13,000
FALSE
This reeks of dramatic licence and mild cliché, from the rain falling into his despair, to the unheard apologies. Plus Saroo never writes about these things happening. 
143
01:30:13,000 --> 01:30:43,000
FALSE
Saroo says at times his search became claustrophobic & of course at times he became discouraged, but he makes no mention of ever freaking out & kicking stuff. & he certainly wasn't in this mood the night he got lucky. 
144
01:30:43,000 --> 01:31:31,000
TRUE
It was in a moment of idle searching & a break from his forensic, methodical approach that he finally found Burhanpur station. 
145
01:31:31,000 --> 01:32:35,000
TRUE-ISH
He didn't do that. He just did a little idle exploring & found the train station quite by chance. He wasn't particularly miserable either. 
146
01:32:35,000 --> 01:33:18,000
TRUE-ISH
It was more that he was idly following a river when he noticed that there were no train tracks, then started looking for the nearest train tracks & on finding them, found the nearest stations & boom! There it was. It was completely unexpected. 
147
01:33:18,000 --> 01:34:42,000
TRUE
He found a station with an overpass (another feature he had always remembered), then noticed the water tank. As he explored the area, the adrenaline came. 
148
01:34:42,000 --> 01:35:39,000
TRUE
From Burhanpur, he traced his home town & the neighbourhood he knew as a boy. He doesn't mention tears at this point, but what the hell. 
149
01:35:39,000 --> 01:36:48,000
TRUE-ISH
What should have been Ganesh Talai was actually Khandwa, which confused him considerably. He only found the name Ganesh Talai a few days later through a Khandwa Facebook group. 
150
01:36:48,000 --> 01:37:44,000
TRUE-ISH
He actually called out to his partner Lisa, who was asleep in the next room. 
151
01:37:44,000 --> 01:38:29,000
TRUE-ISH
He told his dad the next day at work & then his mum that night at dinner at their house. There was enough caution & trepidation on their parts for the celebration to be slightly muted. 
152
01:38:29,000 --> 01:39:18,000
TRUE
